Program: Outlook
Title: 14/01/2010
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p005rc1l
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 15 Jan 2010
Iranian Interrogation Haleh Esfandiari tells Matthew Bannister about her 100 days of solitary confinement in Tehran's notorious Evin prison. Her book is called "My Prison, My Home", published by HarperPress. Albanian Brides for Serbian Farmers Anke Truijen has been to southern Serbia to meet the farmers who have married women from neighbouring Albania because there was a shortage of local brides. My South African Nanny British film maker Mark Rossiter on his quest to find the black nanny who cared for him as a child. Mark's film "White Boy, Black Nanny" will be shown in the UK on Friday 15th January at 7.30 on Channel 4 as part of the First Cut strand. Show less